gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 123, Cavaliers 121
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers nine-game win streak comes to an end as they fall to the 76ers, 123-121. Buddy Hield led the way for the 76ers with 24 points (5-8 3PT FG) and eight assists, while Kelly Oubre Jr. (24 points) and Tyrese Maxey (22 points, nine assists) added a combined 46 points in the victory. Donovan Mitchell tallied 36 points (4-9 3PT FG) and six assists for the Cavaliers in the losing effort. The 76ers have won back-to-back games as they improve to 32-21 on the season, while the Cavaliers fall to 35-17.
